result.execSummary:
The defendant Terri A Moore was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:36 Defendant Terri A Moore in court.  Derek G Dominguez appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Casey LaBarre is sworn as a witness.  Testifies to his employment with Wis Rapids Police Dept.  Executed a search warrant on 12/20/13 at a residence occupied by Jennifer Wilbourn, Jamal Jones and Terri Moore along with others.  Testifies to how he became aware that individuals resided in residence.  Identifies Jennifer Wilbourn in the courtroom, Terri Moore and Jamal Jones are also identified in the courtroom.  Testifies to conversation with Jamal Jones during search warrant execution.  Testifies to heroine found in Jamal Jones' jean pocket and how he determined they were Jones' jeans.  Testifies to testing of substance.  Testifies to green leafy substance found in Jones' bedroom and testing of substance being positive for THC. Testifies green leafy substance found in west bedroom of residence and to it testing positive for THC.  Bedroom was the room of Wilbourn and Moore.  Testifies to conversation with Wilbourn regarding the substance found.  Testifies to conversation with Moore regarding the substance found.  Money was found on Moore as prerecorded buy money, used in cocaine transaction.  

Atty Dickmann cross examines the witness.  Testifies to how he became of test results on substances.  Testifies to drug transaction that took place and what he was told about the transaction.  

Atty Dominguez submits a copy of CCAP conviction of Terri Moore in Portage Co.  Court accepts Exhibit 1.

Court finds probable cause and binds the matter over for ARGN on Moore and Jones.  Court proceeds to ARGN on Wilbourn.  Arraignment scheduled for February 3, 2014 at 09:00 am.
